title: Clinton, Obama and DeSantis Lend Star Power to Tight N.Y. Races
description: A high-profile display of Republican and Democratic efforts illustrates how many of the state’s races have become unexpectedly close, including the governor’s race.
dc:creator: Luis Ferré-Sadurní
media:credit: Jeenah Moon for The New York Times, Alyssa Schukar for The New York Times
media:description: Gov. Kathy Hochul, left, and Representative Lee Zeldin, right, each have about $6 million to spend in the final days of the New York governor’s campaign.
